30/08/2006
ATHENS, Greece -- The public order ministry announced on Tuesday (29 August) that Greece has begun issuing ePassports containing biometric data. 
The new passports include digital images that are contained in a microchip. 
Fingerprints and iris images would be introduced after a related EU ruling. 
The fee for acquiring the new ID documents is 45 euros, 20 euros more than prior travel documents. 
(AFP, Makfax - 29/08/06)
